## Elevator Simulator - Files Created

### Structure
- **`index.html`** — Main page with building container, elevator shafts, floor buttons, and internal elevator panel. Includes model/tool/provider info from info.json.
- **`styles.css`** — Dark-themed visual design with animated elevator cars, glowing buttons, and responsive layout.
- **`script.ts`** — Main entry point: initializes DOM, handles hall/car calls, updates display.
- **`Elevator.ts`** — Elevator class: tracks floor, direction, destinations, movement logic with SCAN algorithm (no direction change until all same-direction requests fulfilled).
- **`Floor.ts`** — Floor class: manages up/down hall call state.
- **`Building.ts`** — Building class: orchestrates elevator assignment (closest idle → same-direction → queued), handles movement timing, door animations, and pending request queue.

### Key Features
1. **Hall buttons** — Up/down per floor (only down on top floor, only up on ground floor)
2. **10 floors (0–9)**, **4 elevators (E0–E3)**, all start idle at floor 0
3. **Animated elevator cars** — Smooth CSS transitions between floors, door open flash animation
4. **Internal panel** — Tab between elevators, see current floor on LED display, select destination floors
5. **Smart dispatch** — Closest idle elevator responds; same-direction elevators pick up on the way; busy requests are queued
6. **SCAN algorithm** — Elevators complete all requests in current direction before reversing

### Build & Run
```sh
# Build
mkdir -p ./dist && bun build ./index.html --outdir ./dist

# Serve
bunx serve -p 8802
```
